ukraine 's pro - western opposition party today insisted that the opposition party would not accept the constitutional reform pushed by former president kuroki before the second round of presidential election .
this constitutional reform will deprive the majority of the presidential powers currently in force .
in the second round of election , the supreme court announced that the election was not effective on november 21 , and the election committee of the central elections commission ordered a reelection to be held on december 26 . the opposition party leader yugansk once again fell into a deadlock with kuroki .
" if the constitutional amendment is passed in the current form , all the powers of the president will be transferred to the congress , which is unacceptable . "
" we hope that the president will appoint the director of intelligence and chief of staff , so that we can eliminate corruption and remove the group that controls the political and business circles in ukraine , " she told reporters .
kuroki , who has close ties with russia , has pushed forward the constitutional amendment before the election because he is worried that the opposition party may win the presidential election .
the opposition legislators yesterday refused to vote on the constitutional amendment proposed by the government , and the parliament was recollected for 10 days .
according to the constitutional amendment , except for the prime minister , defense minister , and foreign minister , all heads of state will be transferred from the president to the congress , and the current forces supporting the government have nearly the majority of seats in the parliament .
according to the content of the amendment , the prime minister , defense minister , and foreign minister appointed by the president have to be approved by the congress , and the parliament can also put forward their candidates .
