japan 's economic growth could slow down next year
as the gap between the appreciation of yen and the widening of the rich and the poor may undermine the harmonious atmosphere of the first half of this year , japan 's economy may slow down and enter 2005 .
after 10 years of stagflation , the high profit of manufacturers and the strong consumer spending have brought japan back to its confidence this year , but analysts have expressed the hope for their support for economic growth to china , and even though the political tension between japan and china has been increasing .
the evidence has gradually shown that the japanese economy may have a short decline in early 2005 , especially if industrial production continues to decline , the manufacturers will adjust their stockpile to avoid overstockpiles .
according to the new statistics adopted recently , japan 's economy in april - june declined slightly in the first quarter of the year , with a growth of 0.1 percent in the first quarter of july to september , and was just in a sluggish state .
at present , economists still have very different views on the rebound of the japanese economy .
the growth rate of the japanese economy is expected to reach 2.3 percent in real terms by the end of next march .
they said that to " recover " in 2005 , the reason is : the us economy has steadily returned to the track of recovery , and the spending of japanese consumers has made up for the slowdown in exports .
another pessimistic view is that the growth rate for the current fiscal year is only 1.8 percent , and the next fiscal year 's growth rate is lower to 0.6% .
they raised the " potential risks " , that is , the profit of the manufacturers did not lead to an increase in personal gain .
