the u.s. commerce department reported today that its exports shrank by 2.3 percent in november , with a trade deficit of 60.3 billion dollars .
the us exports fell to a new low point in the past five months , but at the same time , because the us imports of oil orders increased to $ 14.2 billion , increasing by more than $ 2 billion , and the growth rate reached 1.3 percent , and the imports increased by 1.3 percent , reaching a record high of $ 155.8 billion .
the trade balance has increased by 7.7 percent from the revised us $ 566 billion in october last year , a significant increase of 50.8 percent from the us $ 40 billion in november 1999 .
according to a survey conducted by the nba 's market observation , wall street 's economic scholars forecast that the trade deficit of financial goods and labor would fall to about 53.3 billion us dollars .
although the us dollar is weak and the us products are relatively cheap , the us trade deficit is still expanding .
the ministry of commerce said today that it would put pressure on the us dollar , and once again called on washington to be able to do something in the us - china trade imbalance .
the decline in us exports in november last year was due to a decrease of us $ 1.4 billion in capital goods , including a decrease of 300 million in the export of aircraft and aircraft engine .
