euro zone data show core inflation under control
the euro zone economic data released this week show that the core rate of inflation is still under control , economists said today .
at the same time , the euro zone 's industrial production and french consumer spending are expected to decline .
the european union ( eu ) census and statistics department ( c & sd ) released a report of inflation on the 20 th of this month , which is expected to increase slightly from 2.2% in november to 2.3 percent in december .
however , the increase rate reflects the increase in tobacco tariffs , and the core rate of inflation is expected to remain at 1.9 percent .
the core rate of inflation will be released together with consumer price figures .
economists pointed out that the core rate of inflation in the prices of food , energy , tobacco , and so on has been maintained between 1.6 and 2 percent in the past two years .
the president of the european central bank ( ecb ) , trichet , said on the 13 th that short - term price pressure has been lowered recently .
although inflation will remain at more than 2 percent in the next few months , it may be reduced by the end of this year .
at the same time , another economist said that in view of the slowdown in germany 's growth , the euro zone 's industrial production is expected to decline on november 18 .
industrial production in germany declined by 1.7% in november , while the financial news agency reported that industrial production in the euro zone would drop further by 0.4 percent in november after a 0.5 percent decline in october .
the industrial production of the euro zone is expected to rebound in december , the us bank said .
