undp : unfulfilled commitments to reduce poverty : un
an expert group appointed by the united nations said in a new report that it has promised to provide money to help the poor countries with a view to reducing the world 's extremely poor population by 2010 .
the world 's rich countries have promised to participate in the united nations ' ambitious " millennium development goals " plan , so as to improve the destiny of the world 's poor and suffering population .
however , there are only one - billion people in the world who are living in less than $ 1 - billion a day , and the population of 2.7 - billion is less than $ 2 - billion a day . un experts said that the time for the rich countries to fulfill their commitments is not a few .
" these goals can still be achieved by using the correct mobilization of resources and political will and the reform of the developing countries , " said brown , director of the un development program .
un experts said that the world 's 22 rich countries promise to provide 0.7 percent of their gross domestic product ( gdp ) assistance , but they are currently providing only 0.25 percent of them .
the development experts headed by the former harvard economists , who have been entrusted by un secretary - general annan , have made progress reports , including the elimination of extreme poverty , the popularization of the early - stage education , the reduction of the death rate of children , and the crackdown on aids and other fatal diseases .
the report said : " the practical solution has already existed , the political structure has been established , and the cost is the first time to bear the burden . now it is just a lack of action . "
