china 's largest sea water descending project to zhoushan
xinhua news agency report of december 6 from hangzhou ( by staff reporter pan qiqun ) - the largest sea - crossing project in the mainland of china , which is the largest in scale and a daily volume of 10,000 tons , will be settled in the zhoushan district of zhejiang province .
as far as the residents of zhoushan who are deeply plagued by the water shortage are concerned , the sea water that they have been in the water for a hundred years will soon be turned into the water of the qing dynasty into the homes of thousands of households .
the reporter learned from the relevant departments that the hangzhou water treatment technology development center of the state oceanic administration and the six town governments of the zhoushan district signed an agreement on the cooperation of 10,000 tons of sea water desalination project .
the project is expected to be completed next year , with an investment of $ 50 million and an estimated 10,000 ton of fresh water in the mainland .
zhoushan is one of the cities with relatively serious water shortages in china .
there are 139 small islands in the whole city , and the per capita quantity of fresh water is 601 cubic meters , which is only 25.4 percent of the per capita ownership of zhejiang province , and the problem of water has been plagued by the life of the residents of this island .
for example , in the pretoria area , the transportation of 1,500 tons of fresh water from a town is approaching , and the cost per ton is more than 10 yuan .
the technology of the state oceanic administration 's hangzhou water treatment technology development center , which is responsible for the development of the anti-infiltration and the separation of sea water , is a process for the purpose of using pressure as a driving force , and is the hot spot of the current international sea water desalination research .
a responsible official of the center said that the cost of the anti - infiltration project and the cost of consumption of sea water have been reduced through technical improvement and the transformation of equipment .
the cost of processing the sea water per ton has dropped further on the basis of $ 5 per ton level .
this indicates that the cost of weakening the sea water is close to the prices of tap water and industrial water .
( international ) hungary 's referendum fails to produce results
xinhua news agency , budapest , december 5 ( reporter liu ) hungary on the 5 th held a referendum on the issue of privatization of public health institutions and the double - nationality issue of the hungarian people .
the number of voters who participated in the voting and the number of people who voted against these two issues have not reached the percentage of votes in the law , and the result of the vote is not valid .
according to statistics released by the hungarian national election office on friday night , the number of votes in 99.91 million , accounting for 37.48 percent of the total number of voters in the country .
among them , 191.19 million and 10393 million people voted against the first issue , accounting for 23.87 percent and 12.85 percent of the total number of voters in the country , 151.8 million and 142.6 million , respectively , and 18.8 percent and 17.75 percent of the total number of voters in the country .
according to the relevant laws of hungary , only the number of people who participated in the election is more than 50 percent of the total number of voters in the country , or the number of people who voted against the above - mentioned issue is more than 25 percent of the total number of voters in the country , and the result of the referendum is effective .
before this , the hungarian government and the ruling party had been urging voters to vote against the two issues , while the opposition party called on voters to vote for the election .
it has been reported that this referendum was the lowest percentage of votes cast by the voters in the previous referendum and the election .
after the vote was released , hungarian prime minister jorge sampaio gave a speech to recognize the failure of the national referendum .
he said that the government would take the initiative to formulate national policies and carry out medical and health reforms .
he said that although the number of people who voted for the vote has not reached a set percentage , the voting is beneficial .
he called on the government and congress to consider the outcome of the referendum when formulating relevant laws .
