adb loans support shanxi 's use of coal and coal gas
xinhua news agency , beijing , december 23 ( reporter jiang guocheng ) the reporter learned from the office of the asian development bank ( adb ) on the 23 rd that the adb recently approved a loan of 1.174 billion us dollars to support the construction of a power station in southern shanxi province in the process of using coal .
the coal - fuelled project will use the latest technology to increase the output of coal and coal fields , and will provide fuel for a power station that will soon be built .
according to the project , the project will provide at least 196 million cubic meters of natural gas per year to about 90,000 families , industrial and commercial users .
about 410,000 people in the jincheng district will benefit from it .
shanxi 's coal output accounts for about one - third of the country 's total output .
the total cost of the project is estimated to be 2.37 billion us dollars , of which 20 million us dollars will be provided by the international cooperation bank of japan , and the china construction bank will provide 378 million us dollars in loans .
the two mining / industrial groups in the jincheng district will provide a total of 61.14 million us dollars of share capital .
the us trade and development agency also offered $ 500,000 worth of donations to the project .
the methane obtained from the underground coal layer is called the methane , and the methane produced in the underground coal mining work is called the coal and the methane .
methane is a very vulnerable gas that can explode , so it is necessary to pass through coal production to ensure the safety of the work environment .
removing , collecting , and using methane will reduce greenhouse gas emissions , and will help reduce global warming and climate change .
methane 's greenhouse effect is 21 times that of carbon dioxide .
the use of methane to replace coal can also increase the use of cleaner fuel , improve the efficiency of coal mines , and make the air more clean .
senior project experts of the adb said that the project is expected to provide about 4.5 million tons of carbon dioxide emissions .
