shenzhen will implement " middle water " in some buildings and small areas .
xinhua news agency , guangzhou , december 26 , as a major measure to build a " water - saving " city , shenzhen will carry out the " intermediate water " application in some large - scale buildings and small - scale areas . at present , relevant regulations and regulations are being formulated .
the " middle water " mainly refers to the fact that the water quality of urban sewage or life water is reached a certain standard after treatment , and that the non - drinking water can be used within a certain scope .
the water quality is between the water supply and the discharge of water in the pipeline .
in general , a large amount of use is used in such areas as toilets , toilets , irrigation , roads , washing vehicles , urban spray , and cooling equipment .
a survey conducted by the shenzhen municipal waters affairs bureau shows that in the mid - 1990 s , more than 70 buildings in shenzhen had built a " intermediate water " recovery system , but because of factors such as technology , design , and management , the cost of the " chung shui " recovery was too high , and the construction units had no choice but to give up the use of the facilities .
to let these pipelines really play a role , it is only necessary to spend 300,000 to 400,000 yuan to install the " intermediate water " processing system .
if we make use of more than 70 sets of " middle water " pipes , we will be able to save 3.5 million tons of water for shenzhen every day .
it has been learned that the " chung shui " recovery work in shenzhen city will first be carried out in the building of more than 70 " middle water " recovery systems , and then further spread the experience .
at the same time , the water services department of shenzhen will join hands with the urban planning and construction departments to formulate the " intermediate water " design standards as soon as possible , and also stipulate that the application of " middle water " in some large - scale buildings will be carried out in a mandatory manner .
the " middle water " that has been dealt with will be the first to use in the urban greening irrigation .
