tsunami hits india 's tamil state of tamil nado
xinhua news agency , qinai ( india ) , december 31 ( reporter jiang yaoping ) - - - - - - - - - the thai state of the southeastern part of india - - - - the fishing industry is developed .
the state has a 1,000 - km - long coastline , with an annual export of 337 - million tons of seafood and a foreign exchange of 2.3 - billion us dollars ( 1 - dollar convertibility ) to the local government .
however , a rare big tsunami caused by the strong earthquake in the indian ocean on the 26 th caused unprecedented damage to local fishery production .
according to an authoritative source of the fisheries industry in the capital of the tamil state , the sudden disaster had a great impact on the fishery production of the state .
because the fishing boats were parked in the harbour without prior warning and preparation .
as a result , more than 7,000 barges and more than 30,000 barges were damaged , accounting for over 80 percent of all ships , and more than 30,000 more than 30,000 fishing nets were damaged .
in an interview with this reporter on the 31 st , the responsible person of the qinai fisheries federation said that even if the fishing boat was good , the fishermen had not dared to go to the sea in the past few months , because they had seen the havoc and brutality of the sea with their own eyes .
some people have bitterly lost their relatives , and some people have their property damaged , and their psychological fears will be left for a long period of time .
it is estimated that the fishing output of the state in 2005 will decrease by about 30 percent over 2004 .
on the 26 th of the tsunami disaster , most of the coastal fishing villages in the state of tamil , were hit and became the most seriously affected area of india .
as of 30 , more than 6230 people have died in the state , and most of them are fishermen .
about 680,000 people were affected by the tsunamis , of which 85 percent were engaged in fishery production .
at present , the indian government is actively carrying out rescue work to restore local fishermen 's livelihood and fishery production as soon as possible .
