( international ) chinese scientific expedition team to reach highest point in antarctic ice cap
xinhua news agency , ueroa , argentina , 8 jan ( xinhua ) -- zhang zhanhai , leader of the chinese 21 st antarctic expedition team , said on 8 january that the chinese scientific expedition team has overcome many difficulties , reaching about 50 km from the antarctic ice cap , and it is estimated that china will be successful in the next two days , thus becoming the first country in the world .
zhang zhanhai told xinhua reporters that one of the important purposes of the " ice - qiong " inspection is to make preparations for the establishment of the third china scientific research station in the antarctic in the future , and to establish a climate monitoring system between the zhongshan station and the " ice . "
a total of 13 members of the ice cap team , the 54 - year - old age group and the youngest is 26 , with an average age of 40 .
seven of them participated in the antarctic inspection earlier , and three of them participated in the inspection of the high - altitude ice in the country .
zhang zhanhai said that the ice - covered examinations were basically carried out according to the plan , but they encountered many difficulties during the period .
the biggest test was that one of the eight refrigerators was split up because of the mechanical cause of the breakup , and the entire team was unable to continue to advance .
for this reason , all members of the team had no choice but to return to 60 km , and they continued to move forward after the new snowstorm .
another problem is altitude reaction .
many of the team members flew to the mountain at a high altitude of 3,800 meters , and the reaction was quite clear , and they were very anxious to cause shortness of breath .
relying on the spirit of unity and struggle , the scientific expedition team defeated many difficulties on the road of advance .
